BFN 

  [Text] It is reported that Kim Pyong-il, North Korean 
President Kim Il-song's second son, has recently assumed an 
important post in military affairs. 
  Western sources in Beijing who are well versed in North 
Korean affairs have reported: It has been learned that Kim 
Pyong-il--whose activities inside North Korea have not been 
known since he returned to Pyongyang last April, one month after 
he went to Finland as ambassador--has been appointed to an 
important post in North Korean military affairs. 

